message.content: cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.COMM, cs.SY - This paper deals with the integration of mmWave communication for access and backhaul in 5G cellular networks, which falls under the domain of network infrastructure and communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves the analysis of bandwidth partitioning and downlink rate coverage probability, which can be categorized under cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking). Additionally, the use of mmWave communication is a key aspect of the paper, which can be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper also involves the study of the performance of the integrated access and backhaul architecture, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control).
